{"name": "weblinx-browsergym", "metadata": {"name": "weblinx-browsergym", "version": "0.0.1.dev14", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/McGill-NLP/weblinx_browsergym", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["tqdm", "huggingface-hub", "numpy", "datasets", "Pillow", "playwright", "browsergym-core", "lxml", "gymnasium"], "summary": "BrowserGym integration for the WebLINX benchmark", "upload_time": 1731618293}, "documentation": ["\n# BrowserGym integration for the WebLINX benchmark\n\nThis package provides a BrowserGym environment for the WebLINX benchmark. It is built on top of the [BrowserGym](https://www.github.com/ServiceNow/browsergym) and [WebLINX](https://www.github.com/McGill-NLP/weblinx) packages.\n\n## Installation\n\nTo install the package, run:\n    \n```bash\npip install weblinx-browsergym\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "weblinx_browsergym.version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "weblinx_browsergym.version.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym.tasks", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "weblinx_browsergym.apply_zoom_to_extra_properties", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "extra_properties", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "zoom", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "inplace", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym.parse_function_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func_str", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym.map_args_to_kwargs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "arg_order", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["The action string in BrowserGym is a string that looks like a function call in Python, e.g.\nclick('251d0ba4-b4d7-4d52')\nsend_msg_to_user(\"Hi! How can I assist you today?\")\n\nWe want to convert this string into the keyword arguments format, i.e.\nclick(uid='251d0ba4-b4d7-4d52')\nsend_msg_to_user(text=\"Hi! How can I assist you today?\")"]}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym.convert_weblinx_to_browsergym_action", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "intent", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "args", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "warn_on_unknown", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This converts an action using the BrowserGym structure to the WebLINX format,\nwhich is different. The mapping of weblinx to browsergym is as follows:\n\nsay(speaker=\"assistant\", utterance=[str]) -> send_msg_to_user(text=[str])\nclick(uid=[element id]) -> click(bid=[element id])\nhover(uid=[element id]) -> hover(bid=[element id])\ntextinput(uid=[element id], value=[str]) -> fill(bid=[element id], value=[str])\nchange(uid=[element], value=[str]) -> \u274c\nload(url=[link]) -> goto(url=[link])\nsubmit(uid=[element]) -> click(bid=[element id])\nscroll(x=[int x],y=[int y]) -> scroll(delta_x=[int x], delta_y=[int y])\ncopy(uid=[element],text=[str]) -> \u274c\npaste(uid=[element],text=[str]) -> \u274c\ntabcreate() -> new_tab()\ntabremove(target=[tabId]) -> tab_close()\ntabswitch(origin=[origin tabId],target=[target tabId]) -> tab_focus(index=[target tabid])"]}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym.convert_browsergym_to_weblinx_action", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "intent", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "args", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "warn_on_unknown", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This converts an action using the BrowserGym structure to the WebLINX format,\nwhich is different. The mapping of weblinx to browsergym is as follows:\n\nsend_msg_to_user(text=[str]) -> say(speaker=\"assistant\", utterance=[str])\nclick(bid=[element id]) -> click(uid=[element id])\nhover(bid=[element id]) -> hover(uid=[element id])\nfill(bid=[element id], value=[str]) -> textinput(uid=[element id], value=[str])\ngoto(url=[link]) -> load(url=[link])\nscroll(delta_x=[int x], delta_y=[int y]) -> scroll(x=[int x],y=[int y])\nnew_tab() -> tabcreate()\ntab_close() -> tabremove(target=[tabId])\ntab_focus(index=[target tabid]) -> tabswitch(origin=[origin tabId],target=[target tabId])"]}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym.download_metadata", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cache_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "repo_id", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "skip_if_exists", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym.list_tasks", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "split", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "cache_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "metadata_path", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym.extract_demo_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "task_name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "weblinx_browsergym.get_unique_demo_ids", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tasks", "type": nu